cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CY

This paper deals with the security vulnerabilities in V2I communications and the strategic misbehavior of individual vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves game theory and strategic interaction between the vehicle classes and the operator, which suggests the category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of V2I communications in highway operations implies the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the study of incentives and equilibrium analysis, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the inspection strategy of the operator, which suggests the category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
